# TypeScript Standards

## Runtime and layout

- **Bun** for backend, bot, website, and tooling
- Shared contracts live in `packages/shared` — API types, dispatch shapes, telemetry interface
- Apps import from `@haulbot/shared` (or project alias); never copy-paste types across apps

## Clean code

```typescript
// ❌ Duplicate handler logic in bot and backend
// ✅ Single orchestration function in backend; bot calls HTTP API

// ❌ any for dispatch_state payloads
// ✅ Export DispatchState, ActiveLeg from packages/shared
```

- Prefer explicit return types on public API and shared exports
- Fail closed on auth, entitlements, and incomplete onboarding
- Errors: typed errors or structured `{ code, message }` — never swallow catches

## Imports

- No circular dependencies — `fallow dead-code --circular-deps` must stay clean
- Backend must not import from `apps/website` or `apps/bot`
- Website/bot must not import backend internals — use HTTP client + shared types

## Tests

- Test behavior that can regress (onboarding resolver, handoff state transitions, Hard Rules eval)
- Skip trivial "renders without crash" tests
